As of the 2022-2023 academic year, the in-state tuition cost for upper division students in the College of Literature, Science, and the Arts (LSA) at the University of Michigan is approximately $16,350 per year for full-time students. This tuition cost is for undergraduate students who have completed at least 55 credit hours and have declared a major within the LSA. It's important to note that this tuition cost does not include additional fees, room and board, or other expenses such as textbooks or personal expenses, which can vary depending on the student's individual situation and choices.